    {
      "id": "b67889c6-463c-4b86-9b1b-47fb8e2428c4",
      "type": "description",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Soit $A$ un polynôme à coefficients réels de degré 2 donné.\nAu polynôme $P$ de degré inférieur ou égal à $2n$ on fait correspondre le\npolynôme $Q = AP' - nA'P$.",
        "html": "<p>Soit <span class=\"math inline\">\\(A\\)</span> un polynôme à coefficients réels de degré 2 donné. Au polynôme <span class=\"math inline\">\\(P\\)</span> de degré inférieur ou égal à <span class=\"math inline\">\\(2n\\)</span> on fait correspondre le polynôme <span class=\"math inline\">\\(Q = AP&#39; - nA&#39;P\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "f001c0ee-f8a1-47cd-bad6-a4a6cf91e1de",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Montrer qu'on définit ainsi un endomorphisme $\\Phi$ de $\\R_{2n}[X]$.",
        "html": "<p>Montrer qu’on définit ainsi un endomorphisme <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\Phi\\)</span> de <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\R_{2n}[X]\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "8847fd52-0dae-4bc9-9b7e-ba21304f5ce1",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Chercher les valeurs propres et les vecteurs propres de $\\Phi$ dans les\n    cas particuliers :\\par\n   \\begin{enumerate}",
        "html": ""
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "54421590-a567-46ed-b0af-78373975d71f",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$A = X^2-1$,",
        "html": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(A = X^2-1\\)</span>,</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "c586a507-75ad-4508-b98a-89366ca747e3",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$A = X^2$,",
        "html": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(A = X^2\\)</span>,</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "a7f20285-9edd-4edb-8134-279648783e3f",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$A = X^2+1$.",
        "html": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(A = X^2+1\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "cb0f9b63-9796-4482-9292-145585e920d7",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$\\lambda = 2k$, $P = \\alpha(X-1)^{n-k}(X+1)^{n+k}$ pour $-n \\le k \\le n$.\n$\\lambda = 0$, $P = \\alpha X^{2n}$.\n$\\lambda = 0$, $P = \\alpha (X^2+1)^n$.",
        "html": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\lambda = 2k\\)</span>, <span class=\"math inline\">\\(P = \\alpha(X-1)^{n-k}(X+1)^{n+k}\\)</span> pour <span class=\"math inline\">\\(-n \\le k \\le n\\)</span>. <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\lambda = 0\\)</span>, <span class=\"math inline\">\\(P = \\alpha X^{2n}\\)</span>. <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\lambda = 0\\)</span>, <span class=\"math inline\">\\(P = \\alpha (X^2+1)^n\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    }
